### CVE-2024-35795 - Patch Information

#### Summary
- **CVE Identifier**: CVE-2024-35795
- **Title**: drm/amdgpu: fix deadlock while reading mqd from debugfs
- **Affected Component**: AMD GPU driver in the Linux kernel

#### Recommended Patches
- The patch addresses a deadlock issue that occurs while reading the queued message descriptor (mqd) from the debug filesystem (debugfs) within the AMD GPU driver (amdgpu).

#### Patch Details
- **Commit Reference**: 
  - The fix is part of the Linux kernel stable tree.
- **Code Example**:
  ```c
  // Sample code snippet illustrating the patch that resolves the deadlock
  // This is a hypothetical representation. Actual code may vary.

  void amdgpu_mqd_create(struct amdgpu_device *adev) {
      // Code before fix
      mutex_lock(&mqd->lock);

      // Deadlock prevention code
      if (mqd->is_reading) {
          // handle reading state safely
          return;  
      }

      // Code that reads mqd from debugfs
      ...
      mutex_unlock(&mqd->lock);
  }
  ```
- **Commit Message**: 
  - "drm/amdgpu: fix deadlock while reading mqd from debugfs"

#### Patch Location
- The patch can be found in the Linux kernel repository:
