  - **Description**: Added authorization checks to ensure only users with the appropriate capabilities can update plugin settings.

#### Code Example

Here is a code snippet demonstrating the added authorization check:

```php
if ( current_user_can( 'manage_options' ) ) {
    // Proceed with updating settings
    update_option( 'my_plugin_setting', $_POST['my_plugin_setting'] );
} else {
    // User does not have permission
    wp_die( 'You do not have sufficient permissions to access this page.' );
}
```

