The exploitation of CVE-2024-47744 primarily focuses on manipulating thread synchronization mechanisms to induce deadlocks, resulting in denial of service and potential exploitation of additional vulnerabilities. Proper mutex management is crucial to prevent such scenarios in a multi-threaded environment like the Linux kernel.
